data.description: This home was bought as new construction only 2 years ago! Home has 4 bedrooms and a yard that is almost 1/3 acre! It is on a quiet cul-de-sac in the highly sought after city of Basehor due to its great schools, small town feel, and distance from Kansas City.  The subdivision is on the north side of Basehor and is close to the county line so has a country feel to it. The home is within walking distance to the highly sought after new elementary school, Grayhawk Elementary.  The subdivision includes a pool, basketball court and shelters with picnic tables. Upgrades of the home include a wood privacy fence with 2 gates, tiled master shower with soft touch glass door, 3 stage filtration system so not only are you drinking filtered water, but there is no hard water through the home! Other upgrades include 3 Canadian Plums trees, 1 Colorado Spruce, 1 Red Sunset Maple. The seeded backyard has fully matured so the task of growing it is already done for you! There is a nice covered deck for you to enjoy on hot summer nights.  Move in ready for your children and pups with the fenced yard! Please allow 24 hour notice for showing on week days before 4 pm. After 4 pm on week days and any time on weekends, home can be shown on short notice.
